# 🚀 Day 69/90 – Connect the Report Screen to the Data Model

Welcome to **Day 69!**

Yesterday, we created our first **BloodReport model**.

Today we'll use that model to display data on the Report Details screen instead of hard-coded values.

This is how professional Flutter apps are built.

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

Instead of writing:

```dart
"Hemoglobin"
"13.8 g/dL"
```

We'll use:

```dart
sampleReport.hemoglobin
```

This means later, when OCR extracts real values, we only need to replace the sample data—the UI won't need to change.

